                      <span>2001-05-06</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>It was difficult to stop reading the book, once I started. This collection of interviews with the idealists, the activists, the real "fighters" in the civil rights movement in the 50s and 60s -- and the people who stood against them -- is an empowering, educational read.  Truly, this book is a must for those interested in learning more about the civil rights struggle (a struggle that continues until today), and about movements for peace and social justice in general.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A "must-have" book on the civil rights movement.</div>
